on the Macha of Armagh, in current spelling making it Mhacha.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div style="clear:both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>Ard Mhacha or Ard Macha?</title><link>http://talkirish.com/forums/thread/6718.aspx</link><pubDate>Sat, 16 Jul 2011 14:34:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">0644754f-ff87-49dd-b5e3-0e104f790f4a:6718</guid><dc:creator>Armaghgeddon</dc:creator><slash:comments>0</slash:comments><comments>http://talkirish.com/forums/thread/6718.aspx</comments><wfw:commentRss>http://talkirish.com/forums/commentrss.aspx?SectionID=7&amp;PostID=6718</wfw:commentRss><description>&lt;p&gt;Why is Armagh in irish spelt in two different ways?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div style="clear:both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>